ohha.puzzlecrafter.auxiliary

Class IsDuplicated

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohha.puzzlecrafter.auxiliary.IsDuplicated

  • public final class IsDuplicated
extends Object
    Provides a slew of static methods for testing whether a cell's value is unique in its row, column or region.

    • Method Detail

      • onRow

        public static boolean onRow(Grid grid,
                            CellCoordinate c)
        Returns whether a cell's value is unique on its row. Uniqueness is only tested if the cell's value is filled in (see Grid). Undetermined and empty are considered non-values, and the method returns false whether the cell is the only undetermined/empty-valued cell on its row or not.
        Parameters:
        grid - the grid to test on
        c - the coordinate of the cell to test
        Returns:
        returns true if the cell is filled in and unique on its row, and false otherwise

      • onColumn

        public static boolean onColumn(Grid grid,
                               CellCoordinate c)
        Returns whether a cell's value is unique on its column. Uniqueness is only tested if the cell's value is filled in (see Grid). Undetermined and empty are considered non-values, and the method returns false whether the cell is the the only undetermined/empty-valued cell on its column or not.
        Parameters:
        grid - the grid to test on
        c - the coordinate of the cell to test
        Returns:
        returns true if the cell is filled in and unique on its column, and false otherwise

      • onRegion

        public static boolean onRegion(Grid grid,
                               Partition partition,
                               CellCoordinate c)
        Returns whether a cell's value is unique on its region. Uniqueness is only tested if the cell's value is filled in (see Grid). Undetermined and empty are considered non-values, and the method returns false whether the cell is the the only undetermined/empty-valued cell on its region or not.

        The method expects to receive a valid partition (see Partition), in particular it expects that the cell is contained in one of the partition's regions.

        Parameters:
        grid - the grid to test on
        partition - the partition to test on
        c - the coordinate of the cell to test
        Returns:
        returns true if the cell is filled in and unique on its column, and false otherwise
